[30;1m73 | [0m[35m        *timeout* parameter will set the timeout on the socket instance[0m
[30;1m74 | [0m[35m        before attempting to connect.  If no *timeout* is supplied, the[0m
[30;1m75 | [0m[35m        global default timeout setting returned by :func:`socket.getdefaulttimeout`[0m
[30;1m76 | [0m[35m        is used.  If *source_address* is set it must be a tuple of (host, port)[0m

[30;1m936 | [0m[35m    that both proxies and targets have the same behavior when connecting via TLS.[0m
[30;1m937 | [0m[35m    """[0m
[30;1m938 | [0m[35m    default_ssl_context = False[0m

[30;1m1462 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m1401 | [0m[35mHappy Eyeballs (also called Fast Fallback) is an algorithm published by the IETF that[0m
[30;1m1402 | [0m[35mmakes dual-stack applications (those that understand both IPv4 and IPv6) more responsive[0m
[30;1m1403 | [0m[35mto users by attempting to connect using both IPv4 and IPv6 at the same time (preferring IPv6), thus[0m
[30;1m1404 | [0m[35mminimizing common problems experienced by users with imperfect IPv6 connections or setups.[0m
[30;1m1405 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m41 | [0m[35m    the SO_REUSEADDR socket option having different semantics on Windows versus[0m
[30;1m42 | [0m[35m    Unix/Linux.  On Unix, you can't have two AF_INET SOCK_STREAM sockets bind,[0m
[30;1m43 | [0m[35m    listen and then accept connections on identical host/ports.  An EADDRINUSE[0m
[30;1m44 | [0m[35m    OSError will be raised at some point (depending on the platform and[0m

[30;1m46 | [0m[35m[0m
